# Normalise line endings in the repository, and check every text file out with
# LF regardless of platform.
#
# This is not cosmetic. The integration ships shell scripts that must execute
# inside PX4's ROMFS and build (sitl_run.sh, install.sh, uninstall.sh, the two
# sync scripts, detect-px4.sh). A cloner with core.autocrlf=true — the Git for
# Windows default, and WSL is mainstream for PX4 development — would otherwise
# get CRLF, and a `#!/bin/sh\r` shebang fails to exec with a bewildering
# "bad interpreter: No such file or directory".
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt and braces for the executable payload: these must be LF even if someone
# adds a conflicting rule above.
*.sh            text eol=lf
ROMFS/px4fmu_common/init.d-posix/airframes/* text eol=lf

# CMake and Python are read by tools that also dislike stray CRLF.
*.cmake         text eol=lf
CMakeLists.txt  text eol=lf
*.py            text eol=lf
*.json          text eol=lf

# Let git treat sources and docs as text, with LF.
*.cpp           text eol=lf
*.h             text eol=lf
*.md            text eol=lf
